Add leads to the user's transient selection (used by selection-scoped bulk operations). Accepts 1-1000 `leadIds` per call.

{{include:headers/tool-when-to-use}} low-level. The user's selection is a per-token global state — be careful when invoking directly.

{{include:headers/tool-when-not-to-use}} in normal flow — leadbay_enrich_titles wraps select → action → clear in one call with proper Mutex protection. Calling this directly without acquiring the selection lock can clobber concurrent composite calls.

{{include:headers/verification-required-if-write}}
